total of 212 patients seeking hypertension care at five public
facilities were interviewed, and information on care seeking and
the associated costs was obtained. We computed both annual
direct and indirect costs borne by these patients. RESULTS:
Overall, the mean annual direct cost to patients was US$ 304.8
